uals found it increasingly relevant to their situation. By 1318 John had ordered an investigation which led to the report of an eight-man commission in 1319. He then submitted particular passages from Oivi's commentary to individual theologians before he himself condemned it in 1326. Those are the facts. In this book David Burr reconsiders their significance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Sep 2021) 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / New Testament.2bisacsh  aMedieval and Renaissance Studies.  aReligion.  aReligious Studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Press Package Archive 1898-1999z978311044252640uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/978151280094440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781512800944423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781512800944/original  a978-3-11-044252-6  University of Pennsylvania Press Package Archive 1898-1999c1898d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK